---
apiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1
kind: PrometheusRule
metadata:
  name: longhorn-snapshots
  namespace: monitoring
spec:
  groups:
    - name: longhorn-snapshots
      rules:
        - alert: LonghornVolumeSnapshotCountHigh
          expr: count by (volume) (longhorn_snapshot_actual_size_bytes) > 40
          for: 30m
          labels:
            severity: warning
          annotations:
            summary: "Longhorn volume {% raw %}{{ $labels.volume }}{% endraw %} has too many snapshots"
            description: >-
              Longhorn volume {% raw %}{{ $labels.volume }}{% endraw %} has {% raw %}{{ $value }}{% endraw %} snapshots,
              which is well above the expected steady state (~25 for the default
              hourly recurring job with retain 24). This often indicates snapshots
              that are no longer being pruned by retention (for example, snapshots
              left behind by a renamed or deleted recurring job). The volume's
              snapshot-max-count cap is {{ longhorn_snapshot_max_count }}; once reached, Longhorn stops creating
              new snapshots and recurring snapshot jobs and replica rebuilds may
              be affected. Investigate and remove stale snapshots.
        - alert: LonghornVolumeSnapshotCountCritical
          expr: count by (volume) (longhorn_snapshot_actual_size_bytes) > {{ longhorn_snapshot_max_count - 2 }}
          for: 1h
          labels:
            severity: critical
          annotations:
            summary: "Longhorn volume {% raw %}{{ $labels.volume }}{% endraw %} is at the snapshot cap"
            description: >-
              Longhorn volume {% raw %}{{ $labels.volume }}{% endraw %} has {% raw %}{{ $value }}{% endraw %} snapshots and
              is at or near the snapshot-max-count cap of {{ longhorn_snapshot_max_count }}. Once the cap is
              reached, Longhorn stops creating new snapshots, so recurring
              snapshot data protection silently stops and replica rebuilds may be
              affected. Remove stale snapshots now to restore headroom.
